        jTextArea1.setText("\n - Click the 'check-box' at the end of each line to commit data to the database, uncheck to edit.\n\n - After submitting a form a print option will show in the middle of your screen.\n\n - If you wish to clear a line of data, type in the number in the bottom left field next to the clear line button. \n   Once you confirm the line clear it will delete all the data on that line from the application and the \n   database. \n   THIS CANNOT BE REVERSED! So make sure you really want to clear that line before confirming.\n\n - Admin Panel is meant for the Store to be able to see all the forms they are working on and any forms submitted \n   to 'DL' or 'IC' for approval. As a Store you will only be able to open the forms at 'In-Process' status but you can \n   view all data with the 'view all' button at the bottom of the 'Admin Panel' window. The 'DL' will use this panel with \n   a password to open the store submitted NEBAS & EBAS forms for approval. \n\n - Cycle Count Report will allow you to view all the IAS skus that are still in your inventory for your store and \n   you will be able to print a physical copy to the local printer.\n\n - Physical Inventory Report will list all EBAS/NEBAS skus still in your inventory.\n\n - Please close the Application after EVERY use, DO NOT LEAVE THE IAN APP OPEN! If you walk away to help \n   a customer CLOSE THE APP...it only takes a few seconds to open the IAN App back up. Doing this should\n   reduce the chance of your data becoming corrupt having printing issues. The application has a 45 minute timeout \n   if the program is idle. This timeout will cause the program to be UNRESPONSIVE and NO DATA will be DISPLAYED\n   or SAVED. If the Application has any errors or is unresponsive please close the application and reopen it again.\n   If this does not work or If you would like to make a suggestion please email Tamara Katheiser at \n   tkatheiser@cyclegear.com\n   \n  *** After CLOSING the application YOU MUST LOG OUT of the Citrix store desktop from the START menu ***\n\n   Thank you,\n   Warren Stevens   IAN Developer");
